narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained new insights into the variety of tools and weapon systems the US Navy has under its control, and how my role as a JO will impact the readiness of sailors/systems under me. Learned about cool stuff like EM jamming devices, the physical underpinnings, etc.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Semi-interesting material (except for the cyber domain stuff), engaging and humorous lecturer, low workload compared to other classes. Weaknesses: Required as a NROTC midshipman, early class hours (7:25 ish start), powerpoint slide presentation is bland/unwieldy.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Take this class if interested in learning about missiles, rockets, how electronic jamming works, etc, in a casual, laid-back environment. Don't take if mornings are not your thing. Waking up to walk in the cold and darkness early in the semester is not fun.
